The president's "Czar of cryptocurrencies", the investor of Silicon Valley David Sacks, convened important founders, CEOs and investors to develop policies aimed at speeding up the growth of cryptocurrencies and providing the legitimacy that the sector longed for. Among the guests will be the Cameron and Tyler Winklevoss twins, > founders of the Gemini platform, Brad Armstrong of Coinbase and Michael Saylor, the chief investor of bitcoin MicroStrategy. On the rebirth of cryptocurrencies the fate of FTX, once the main exchange of cryptocurrencies that collapsed dramatically when it was discovered that the caeus, Sam Bankman-Fried, who is now serving a 25-year sentence, had faded customers.&nbsp;
