The law enforcement forces see digital activities as a means to recycle illicit money and another challenge is represented by the proliferation of "memecoin", cryptocurrencies based on celebrities, memes of the Internet or pop culture >piuttosto that on technical utility. Much of the cryptocurrency industry disapproves this practice because it fears that it dispels the business, among reports of rapid pump-and-dump schemes that leave unaware buyers to pay for activities that end up being worthless.
Despite his previous hostility towards cryptocurrencies, Trump embraced technology, declaring his intention to make the United States a world power.> Its administration has already adopted significant measures to overcome regulatory obstacles and has confirmed plans for a strategic reserve of cryptocurrencies in which the U.S. government would deposit investments in digital currency acquired mainly from judicial seizures. &nbsp;
Jacob Phillips of Lombard Finance defined this potential move "one of the strongest approvals that the industry has ever seen", observing that several founders and teams have already moved to the United States thanks to the improvement of the regulatory climate. Trump also appointed crypto supporter Paul Atkins at the head of the Securities and Exchange Commission and under him the SEC abandoned legal actions against major platforms such as Coinbase and Kraken initiated during Biden's mandate.
