Some parliamentarians hesitate, disturbed by scandals and recurring reports of market collapses, thefts and scams. The recent $1.5 billion theft from the Bybit platform underlines the risks that cryptocurrencies present> and however, Dante Disparte di Circle, which issues the stablecoin USDC anchored to the dollar, sees a growing bipartisan support for cryptocurrency legislation that attributes to proposals that include strong transparency and anti-money laundering requirements along with consumer protection and market.&nbsp;

