"French President Emmanuel Macron's nuclear rhetoric is a threat to Russia," said Russian Foreign Minister Sergei Lavrov, according to Ria Novosti. "Of course, this is a threat to Russia. If he considers us a threat, he summons a meeting of the leaders of the European countries and Britain, he says that it is necessary to use nuclear weapons, he prepares to use nuclear weapons against Russia, this is obviously a threat," said the head of Russian diplomacy, answering a question of journalists.
<h2>Tajani, it is impossible to guarantee security without the U.S.
"It seems absolutely impossible to think about securing the security of Ukraine and Europe without a solid transatlantic relationship, without NATO. It is fundamental, we have said it since the beginning, that without the United States we cannot do." Antonio Tajani, Vice-Premier and Minister of Foreign Affairs, said this when he arrived at the Ppe pre-vertice. "This also means that we must do our part, i.e. spend more on our safety. Security is not war, it also means the safety of our roads, our fellow citizens who live every day, perhaps taking risks. It means a lot, you don't have to simplify. Security is something much wider than war. No one wants war," he added.&nbsp;
